result.execSummary:
The defendant Cody Raymond Roskowiak was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Cody Raymond Roskowiak is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Cody Raymond Roskowiak was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Fox, ADA:  Kenneth N. Sortedahl,  DF ATTY:  John A. Kucinski,  DF:  Cody Raymond Roskowiak appeared. Includes 14CF383, 14TR3259 and 14TR3260. There is an agreement. Court reviews constitutional rights with def. Court finds def freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights. Court reads charge and possible penalties for count 3 in 14CF383. Def pleads GUILTY.  Court uses complaints/reports as factual basis, accepts plea and adjudicates def guilty of count 3. Counts 1 & 2 are dismissed. Court orders: court costs of $243.00.
Defendant is advised of right to appeal. 
RE: 14TR3259 - GGP/G Court orders: $761.50 forfeiture, 6 months drivers license revocation, AODA and follow all recommendation and driver safety plan. 
It is noted that PAC under .15 therefore ignition interlock is not ordered. 
Court dismisses 14TR3260.
Payment plan is approved.
Defendant is eligible for expungement under 973.105; upon defendant's request after 1 to 2 years pending no further violations.

Pre-trial conference on November 3, 2014 at 09:45 am.

It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Rivers Edge Campground or Diner.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
